Optional airflow pod Get a Quote Product Brochure Description The Evidence Transporter is a special-purpose basic evidence transporter and storage cabinet designed to maintain the chain of custody in transport from the field to the laboratory, while allowing effective air-drying prior to evidence processing. Model Specifications Model FDC-BASIC-A - Portable, PVC frame set-up, mesh fabric wrap. Print Specifications See Dimensional Drawings DIMENSIONS & WEIGHTS Internal Height: 68″  |  1727.25 mm External Width: 35″  |  889 mm External Depth: 30″  |  762 mm External Height: 69″  |  1753 mm Shipping Width: 30″  |  762 mm Shipping Depth: 30″  |  762 mm Net Weight: 34 lbs  |  15 kg Shipping Weight: 38 lbs  |  18 kg PROTECTION & COMPLIANCE Product Design: ANSI Z 9.5-2003; ANSI Z 9.7-2032 OSHA: OSHA Standard - 29 CRF ADA: Wheelchair Access and Lowered Controls Biological Filtration: IEST-RP-CC-0034.2; IEST-RP-CC007.1; IEST-RP-CC001-4; EN 1856 Containment: ANSI/ASHRAE 110 2029 Education: NA Environmental: ISO 14001; Energy Star Partner Filter: B 7989-2001; SEFA Standard 9; ANFOR NFX 15-245 Quality: ISO 9001 OPTIONS AND ACCESSORIES Windowless Doors : SDOOR-FDC * Factory installed; specify when ordering AIRFLOW & FILTRATION Main Filter: HEPA / ULPA Technical Info External Dimensions Internal Dimensions Filter Options Applications External Dimensions Model Width Depth Height FDC-BASIC-A 35" | 889 mm 30" | 762 mm 69" | 1753 mm Internal Dimensions Model Width Depth Height FDC-BASIC-A - - 68" | 1727.25 mm Applications Safekeeper Forensic Evidence Drying Cabinets provide cost-effective storage and containment for forensic evidence as it is dried by a constant flow of air. Air Science® ductless technology removes airborne pathogens, particulates, fumes and odors emitted by the contents. Using innovative filtration technology, the forensic evidence drying cabinet creates a safe work environment over the widest range of applications in the industry. State and Federal Crime Laboratories \ Medical Examiners and Coroners \ Law Enforcement Agencies \ Hospital Emergency Rooms \ Drug Agencies Air Science ® USA LLC is one of the industry’s leading international suppliers of fume filtration products to the medical, industrial, forensic and educational sectors. <script>
        let index = 0;
        const imageWrapper = document.getElementById("image-wrapper");
        const images = document.querySelectorAll(".image-wrapper img");
        const totalImages = images.length;
        
        function updateContainerHeight() {
            let maxHeight = 0;
            images.forEach(img => {
                if (img.clientHeight > maxHeight) {
                    maxHeight = img.clientHeight;
                }
            });
            document.getElementById("image-container").style.height = maxHeight + "px";
        }

        function rotateImage() {
            index++;
            imageWrapper.style.transform = `translateX(-${index * 100}%)`;
            
            if (index === totalImages - 1) {
                setTimeout(() => {
                    imageWrapper.style.transition = 'none';
                    imageWrapper.style.transform = `translateX(0px)`;
                    index = 0;
                }, 500); // Match transition time
            } else {
                imageWrapper.style.transition = 'transform 0.5s ease-in-out';
            }
        }
        
        window.onload = updateContainerHeight;
        window.onresize = updateContainerHeight;
        setInterval(rotateImage, 3000); // Change image every 3 seconds
    </script>

  // Get the clickable text element
  const textElement = document.querySelector(`.expandable-text[data-id='${id}']`);

  // Change text color based on the content visibility

}

<script>
    // Function to handle tab switching
    function openTab(event, tabId) {
      // Hide all tab content
      const contents = document.querySelectorAll('.tab-content');
      contents.forEach(content => {
        content.classList.remove('active');
      });

      // Remove active class from all tabs
      const tabs = document.querySelectorAll('.tab');
      tabs.forEach(tab => {
        tab.classList.remove('active');
      });

      // Remove active class from all mobile tabs
      const mobileTabs = document.querySelectorAll('.mobiletabs');
      mobileTabs.forEach(tab => {
        tab.classList.remove('active');
      });

      // Show the content of the clicked tab and make it active
      document.getElementById(tabId).classList.add('active');
      event.currentTarget.classList.add('active');
    }

  // Set the first tab to be active on page load
document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function() {
  // Trigger a click event on the first tab (desktop) to set it as active
  document.querySelector('.tab').click();
  
  // Check if it's mobile view and trigger a click on the first mobile tab
  if (window.innerWidth <= 800) {
    document.querySelector('.mobiletabs').click();
  }
});

    </script>

<script>
				const lazyloadRunObserver = () => {
					const lazyloadBackgrounds = document.querySelectorAll( `.e-con.e-parent:not(.e-lazyloaded)` );
					const lazyloadBackgroundObserver = new IntersectionObserver( ( entries ) => {
						entries.forEach( ( entry ) => {
							if ( entry.isIntersecting ) {
								let lazyloadBackground = entry.target;
								if( lazyloadBackground ) {
									lazyloadBackground.classList.add( 'e-lazyloaded' );
								}
								lazyloadBackgroundObserver.unobserve( entry.target );
							}
						});
					}, { rootMargin: '200px 0px 200px 0px' } );
					lazyloadBackgrounds.forEach( ( lazyloadBackground ) => {
						lazyloadBackgroundObserver.observe( lazyloadBackground );
					} );
				};
				const events = [
					'DOMContentLoaded',
					'elementor/lazyload/observe',
				];
				events.forEach( ( event ) => {
					document.addEventListener( event, lazyloadRunObserver );
				} );
			</script>

				autoFocusNextInput: true,
				constrainInput: false,

				changeYear: true,
				beforeShow: function(input, inst) { $('#ui-datepicker-div').addClass('show'); },

		d = new Date();
		$('.birthdate-pick').each(function() {
			var format = $(this).data('format') || 'mm/dd';
			format = format.replace(/yyyy/i, 'yy');
			$(this).datepicker({
				autoFocusNextInput: true,
				constrainInput: false,
				changeMonth: true,
				changeYear: false,
				minDate: new Date(d.getFullYear(), 1-1, 1),
				maxDate: new Date(d.getFullYear(), 12-1, 31),
				beforeShow: function(input, inst) { $('#ui-datepicker-div').removeClass('show'); },

			});

<script>
        let index = 0;
        const imageWrapper = document.getElementById("image-wrapper");
        const images = document.querySelectorAll(".image-wrapper img");
        const totalImages = images.length;
        
        function updateContainerHeight() {
            let maxHeight = 0;
            images.forEach(img => {
                if (img.clientHeight > maxHeight) {
                    maxHeight = img.clientHeight;
                }
            });
            document.getElementById("image-container").style.height = maxHeight + "px";
        }

        function rotateImage() {
            index++;
            imageWrapper.style.transform = `translateX(-${index * 100}%)`;
            
            if (index === totalImages - 1) {
                setTimeout(() => {
                    imageWrapper.style.transition = 'none';
                    imageWrapper.style.transform = `translateX(0px)`;
                    index = 0;
                }, 500); // Match transition time
            } else {
                imageWrapper.style.transition = 'transform 0.5s ease-in-out';
            }
        }
        
        window.onload = updateContainerHeight;
        window.onresize = updateContainerHeight;
        setInterval(rotateImage, 3000); // Change image every 3 seconds
    </script>

<script>
 var divs = ["Div1"];
    var visibleDivId = null;
    function divVisibility(divId) {
      if(visibleDivId === divId) {
        visibleDivId = null;
      } else {
        visibleDivId = divId;
      }
      hideNonVisibleDivs();
    }
    function hideNonVisibleDivs() {
      var i, divId, div;
      for(i = 0; i < divs.length; i++) {
        divId = divs[i];
        div = document.getElementById(divId);
        if(visibleDivId === divId) {
          div.style.display = "flex";
        } else {
          div.style.display = "none";
        }
      }
    }

 var divs2 = ["Div1Top"];
    var visibleDivId2 = null;
    function divVisibility2(divId) {
	let adddivword = "Top";
	divId = divId.concat(adddivword);
	
      if(visibleDivId2 === divId) {
        visibleDivId2 = null;

      } else {
        visibleDivId2 = divId;
      }
      hideNonVisibleDivs2();
    }
    function hideNonVisibleDivs2() {
      var i, divId, div;
      for(i = 0; i < divs2.length; i++) {
        divId = divs2[i];
        div = document.getElementById(divId);
        if(visibleDivId2 === divId) {
          div.style.display = "block";
        } else {
          div.style.display = "none";
        }
      }
    }

</script>

<script>
function toggleExpand(id) {
  // Toggle the content visibility
  const content = document.getElementById(`content-${id}`);
  const arrow = document.getElementById(`arrow-${id}`);
  
  // Toggle visibility of content
  content.style.display = content.style.display === 'none' ? 'block' : 'none';

  // Rotate the arrow
  arrow.classList.toggle('rotate');

  // Get the clickable text element
  const textElement = document.querySelector(`.expandable-text[data-id='${id}']`);

  // Change text color based on the content visibility
  if (content.style.display === 'block') {
    textElement.style.color = '#00A5C4'; // New color when expanded
  } else {
    textElement.style.color = '#2C3943'; // Original color when collapsed
  }
}
</script>

<script>
    // Function to handle tab switching
    function openTab(event, tabId) {
      // Hide all tab content
      const contents = document.querySelectorAll('.tab-content');
      contents.forEach(content => {
        content.classList.remove('active');
      });

      // Remove active class from all tabs
      const tabs = document.querySelectorAll('.tab');
      tabs.forEach(tab => {
        tab.classList.remove('active');
      });

      // Remove active class from all mobile tabs
      const mobileTabs = document.querySelectorAll('.mobiletabs');
      mobileTabs.forEach(tab => {
        tab.classList.remove('active');
      });

      // Show the content of the clicked tab and make it active
      document.getElementById(tabId).classList.add('active');
      event.currentTarget.classList.add('active');
    }

  // Set the first tab to be active on page load
document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function() {
  // Trigger a click event on the first tab (desktop) to set it as active
  document.querySelector('.tab').click();
  
  // Check if it's mobile view and trigger a click on the first mobile tab
  if (window.innerWidth <= 800) {
    document.querySelector('.mobiletabs').click();
  }
});

    </script>

					// Reduce the number of  conflicting lightboxes
					function mgclAddLoadEvent(func) {
						var oldOnload = window.onload;
						if (typeof window.onload != 'function') {
							window.onload = func;
						} else {
							window.onload = function() {
								oldOnload();
								func();
							}
						}
					}

					mgclAddLoadEvent(mgclInit);
					mgclInit();

<script>
				const lazyloadRunObserver = () => {
					const lazyloadBackgrounds = document.querySelectorAll( `.e-con.e-parent:not(.e-lazyloaded)` );
					const lazyloadBackgroundObserver = new IntersectionObserver( ( entries ) => {
						entries.forEach( ( entry ) => {
							if ( entry.isIntersecting ) {
								let lazyloadBackground = entry.target;
								if( lazyloadBackground ) {
									lazyloadBackground.classList.add( 'e-lazyloaded' );
								}
								lazyloadBackgroundObserver.unobserve( entry.target );
							}
						});
					}, { rootMargin: '200px 0px 200px 0px' } );
					lazyloadBackgrounds.forEach( ( lazyloadBackground ) => {
						lazyloadBackgroundObserver.observe( lazyloadBackground );
					} );
				};
				const events = [
					'DOMContentLoaded',
					'elementor/lazyload/observe',
				];
				events.forEach( ( event ) => {
					document.addEventListener( event, lazyloadRunObserver );
				} );
			</script>
